#: .\items.json
msgid "quickheal pill"
msgid_plural "quickheal pills"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'quickheal pill'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"This pseudomagical pill will heal all your damaged parts, but only if "
"consumed while on your sanctuary island. No reason to bring this into the "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "earthbound pill"
msgid_plural "earthbound pills"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'earthbound pill'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"This pseudomagical pill extends the amount of time you can stay earthside by"
" 4 pulses, or about 50% of a normal trip. They're precious, but should help "
"buy time for a difficult extract."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "homeward mote"
msgid_plural "homeward motes"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'homeward mote'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"Though visibly little more than a glowing dustbunny, this strange ethereal mote of warp essence reveals, on closer inspection, something more. A tiny, twisting, half-visible thread of shimmering bluish-purple trails away into the sky and far out of sight, unimpeded by any obstacles.\n"
"\n"
"Taking this rare and valuable artifact with you on an expedition is essentially buying life insurance. If you die with this mote in your inventory, you will instead be restored to full health and brought home WITH all items and equipment carried. But this effect will only last for a single expedition. Even if you extract safely, any and all motes carried on your person when you return home will be DESTROYED."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "skyward beacon"
msgid_plural "skyward beacons"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'skyward beacon'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"This smooth purplish sphere seems like it wants to rise right out of your "
"hand. If you activate it, you will return directly to the island with "
"everything you are carrying."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "warp status crystal"
msgid_plural "warp status crystals"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'warp status crystal'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A small crystalline orb that pulses with a faint inner light. When "
"activated, it displays detailed information about your current warp status, "
"including pulse count, time remaining, and the effects that will occur at "
"each stage of warp sickness."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "warped animal teleporter"
msgid_plural "warped animal teleporters"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'warped animal teleporter'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A hand-sized device with a shimmering portal at its core. Unlike a normal "
"pet carrier, this device doesn't store the animal inside - it warps them "
"directly to your sanctuary island, bypassing any weight limitations. "
"Activate near a friendly creature to send it home. The creature will appear "
"at your island when you return from your expedition."
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "warp home focus"
msgid_plural "warp home foci"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'warp home focus', 'str_pl': 'warp home foci'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A small crystalline focus imbued with the power of warp. When activated during an expedition, it can teleport you directly back to your sanctuary island. This item is NOT consumed on use.\n"
"\n"
"Behavior depends on your difficulty settings:\n"
"- Free mode: Works instantly\n"
"- Shard mode: Costs 1 warp shard, cannot use near enemies\n"
"- Other modes: Does not function (use Skyward Beacon or find extraction)"
msgstr ""

#: .\items.json
msgid "healing salve"
msgid_plural "healing salves"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'healing salve'}
#: .\items.json
msgid ""
"A lump of purplish goo, smooth but yielding, sculptable like clay. If you "
"rub it on a wound, it will immediately heal some of the damage you have "
"taken, but the air of the lower world destabilizes its structure and it will"
" only last a single trip to the surface."
msgstr ""

